description.narrative: (Kenya): This mechanism will build on activities supported during Kenya's 2017 electoral process and address the political process, civic engagement and conflict mitigation emerging after the general election. Interventions may include defending civil society against closing space, strengthening capacity for civic engagement at national and county levels, greater inclusion and representation of youth, women, and marginalized groups, promotion of national dialogue that seeks solutions to root causes of conflict, strengthening conflict mitigation mechanisms at national and local levels, enhancing citizen access to government information and services, and strengthening elections and political processes and systems. A key focus will be to prepare Kenyans and Kenyan institutions to fundamentally address weaknesses experienced before, during, and after the 2017 general elections.
